casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellee, v. Williams, Appellant.*

[Cite as State v. Williams, 9 Ohio App. 2d 196.]

(No. 9866 Decided January 16, 1967.) Mr. Melvin G. Rueger and Mr. Robert K. Sachs, for appellee. Mr. Anthony J. Brueneman, Jr., for appellant.

For opinion on motion to dismiss, see 8 Ohio App. 2d 258.

 Per Curiam.

An examination of the record discloses no error prejudicial to the rights of appellant. The judgment of the Court of Common Pleas of Hamilton County is, therefore, affirmed.

Judgment affirmed.

Hildebrant, P. J., Long and Hover, JJ., concur.
